                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.93/52.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul General at
                            Monterey</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please inform Chinese Minister that thirty-five Chinese are without clothing or
                    food, one wounded as result of late battle. I am supplying them food. The
                    leading one says that 2000 pesos are needed to help clothe and feed them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
